## Security Documentation Standards

### docs/SECURITY.md Requirements

The security documentation MUST include:

1. **OWASP GenAI Top 10 Checklist** — Status of each vulnerability mitigation
2. **Threat Model** — Mermaid diagram of attack surfaces
3. **Authentication & Authorization** — OAuth flows, token lifecycle
4. **Prompt Injection Defense** — Detection patterns, quarantine process
5. **Regression corpus inventory** — Payload and regex pattern counts with `corpus-inventory` marker
6. **Data Classification** — What data flows where, PII handling
7. **Cryptographic Standards** — Algorithms used, key management
8. **Incident Response** — Security event escalation process

### Test Suite Documentation Sync

When tests are added or removed under `backend/tests/`, update counts in **all** of:

| File | What to update |
|---|---|
| `docs/SECURITY.md` | Test suite inventory table + `<!-- test-inventory:total=N -->` |
| `README.md` | Tests badge, feature bullets, tech stack table, tree diagram, quick-start comments + marker |
| `backend/AGENT.md` | Testing Requirements section + marker |
| `AGENT.md` | Workflow rule reference + marker |
| `proposal-case-study.md` | Marker (near input-security section) |
| `SECURITY.md` (root) | Pointer to inventory (if counts cited) |

Verify with: `uv run pytest backend/tests/test_suite_inventory.py`

Get the authoritative count: `uv run pytest --collect-only -q backend/tests`

### Injection Corpus Documentation Sync

When security test vectors change, update counts in **all** of:

| File | What to update |
|---|---|
| `docs/SECURITY.md` | Regression corpus inventory table + `<!-- corpus-inventory:payloads=N,patterns=M -->` |
| `README.md` | Security posture section counts + marker |
| `backend/AGENT.md` | Prompt injection section counts + marker |
| `proposal-case-study.md` | Input security layer table + marker |
| `SECURITY.md` (root) | Pointer to inventory (if counts cited) |
| `docs/learning/week6-owasp-agent-governance.md` | Corpus references (if counts cited) |

Verify with: `uv run pytest backend/tests/security/test_corpus_inventory.py`

