## Documentation Quality Checklist

Before completing documentation updates:

| Check | Description |
|---|---|
| ✅ Accuracy | All code references match actual implementation |
| ✅ Completeness | All required sections present |
| ✅ Currency | Version numbers and dates are current |
| ✅ Test suite inventory | Total pytest collection count matches docs (`test_suite_inventory.py`) |
| ✅ Corpus inventory | Injection payload/pattern counts match code (`test_corpus_inventory.py`) |
| ✅ Links | All internal links resolve correctly |
| ✅ Examples | Code examples are syntactically correct |
| ✅ Diagrams | Mermaid diagrams render correctly |
| ✅ Consistency | Terminology matches glossary |

