## Epic Workflow Position

The Docs Agent runs **last** after all other agents complete:

1. ✅ Coding Agent — Implementation complete
2. ✅ Refactor Agent — Code quality verified
3. ✅ Testing Agent — Tests passing
4. **🔄 Docs Agent — You are here (final)**

### Handoff Checklist (Pre-Merge)

Before epic can be merged to `epic/autonomus-implementation`:
- [ ] All new agents have AGENT.md files
- [ ] docs/PLAN.md updated with ✅ status
- [ ] docs/tasks/todo.md Review section completed
- [ ] Any learnings captured in docs/learning/
- [ ] CHANGELOG.md updated (if applicable)
- [ ] README.md updated (if user-facing changes)

### Post-Merge Tasks

After PR merged to `epic/autonomus-implementation` (via **merge commit**, not squash/rebase):

**GitHub / git:**
- [ ] Checkout and pull `epic/autonomus-implementation`
- [ ] Delete **local** epic branch: `git branch -d epic/E{n}-{short-description}`
- [ ] Do **not** delete the remote epic branch on GitHub

**Documentation:**
- [ ] Update docs/tasks/todo.md Completed Epics table
- [ ] Archive completed task plan
- [ ] Prepare template for next epic
- [ ] Delete active `docs/tasks/checkpoint.md` (if present)

